CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 1, 1941, pg. 24 reads: "Bobby Enjoyed Sixth Birthday - Mr. and Mrs. Spotwood of 603 Herron avenue gave a birthday party in honor of their son, Bobby's sixth birthday. Left to right: George Deakins, Carol Finch, Billy Spotwood, Ellen Finch, Christine Finch, Gert Finch, Audrey Deakins, Collins Terry Jean Spotwood, Bobby Finch, Alberta Deakins. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of children, from left first row: George Deakins, Carol Finch, Billy Spotwood, Ellen Finch, Christine Finch, and Gert Finch; second row: Audrey Deakins, Collins Terry, Jean Spotwood, Bobby Finch, and Alberta Deakins, in domestic interior for birthday party
